olive oil
1 avocado
1 packet pork mince
1 sachet Kiwi Spice Blend
½ tbs honey
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
drizzle white wine vinegar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet garlic aioli

• Slice avocado in half and scoop out flesh.
• In a medium bowl, mash avocado with a drizzle of olive oil and a generous pinch of salt until smooth.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• Cook pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add Kiwi spice blend and the honey and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Meanwhile, in a large bowl combine shredded cabbage mix and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.
• Microwave mini flourtortillas on a microwave-safe plate in 10 second bursts until warmed through.

• Top each tortilla with smashed avocado, cabbage and spiced pork.
• Drizzle over garlic aioli to serve. Enjoy!

ELEVATE ME: If you’ve added extra ingredients to this recipe, dollop over roasted tomato salsa, sprinkle over shredded Cheddar cheese and tear over coriander to serve.